| [sc name="states_get_quotes_third" bg_class="#{bgClass}" state_title="#{stateTitle}" seal_img_url="#{sealUrl}"]
.container.py-3
    .row
        .col
            p.h2.text-uppercase How do tickets affect the cost of car insurance in #{stateTitle}
            p.lead
                | Having tickets will likely increase your car insurance rates. The degree of increase depends on the type of offense. There are serious violations like Hit and Run or DUI that will enhance your car insurance premium by #{ticketAffection.hitAndRunRateIncreasePercent} % and #{ticketAffection.duiRateIncreasePercent} $ respectively. There are also tickets, which do not significantly affect the premium such as #{ticketAffection.cheapest}.
            table.table.table-sm.table-hover.table-borderless.table-striped
                thead
                    tr
                        th Violation
                        th Avg. Monthly Rate
                        th Increase Percent
                        th Insurance Rate Increase
                tbody
                    each item in ticketAffection.data
                        tr(title=`Getting a ticket for ${item.violation} violation will highly likely raise your annual premium by ${item.rateIncreasePercent}% up to ${item.avgRate * 12} $`)
                            td #{item.violation}
                            td #{item.avgRate} $
                            td #{item.rateIncreasePercent} %
                            td #{item.rateIncrease} $

